# Documentation Conventions for Development Agents

## 1. General Documentation

### 1.1 Documentation Structure
- Clear and logical section organization
- Consistent use of titles and subtitles with Markdown levels
- Addition of links to relevant resources

### 1.2 Language and Style
- Professional English usage
- Concise and precise style
- Avoid unnecessary technical jargon
- Maintain consistency in technical vocabulary

## 2. Technical Documentation

### 2.1 APIs and Interfaces
- Complete documentation of endpoints and methods
- Description of parameters and their types
- Usage examples
- Error handling and special cases

### 2.2 Features
- Detailed description of agent capabilities
- Common usage examples
- Known limitations
- Best practices for use

## 3. User Documentation

### 3.1 Usage Guide
- Step-by-step instructions
- Concrete examples
- Tips and tricks
- FAQ

### 3.2 Use Cases
- Typical scenarios
- Best practices
- Workflow examples

## 4. Development Documentation

### 4.1 Code Structure
- Component organization
- Naming conventions
- Configuration file structure

### 4.2 Integration
- Integration instructions
- Required configuration
- Dependencies
- Testing and validation

## 5. Maintenance and Updates

- Version history
- Release notes
- Compatibility
- Migration

## 6. Best Practices

- Keep documentation up to date
- Check consistency
- Test examples
- Make documentation accessible
- Use real examples
- Add screenshots when relevant
- Include references to external resources

## 7. Format and Style

- Use bullet points for instructions
- Highlight warnings and important notes
- Use tables for structured information
- Include code examples with appropriate formatting
- Add links to additional resources

## 8. Documentation Directory Structure

### 8.1 Root Directory
- README.md: Main project documentation
- docs/: Main documentation directory

### 8.2 Main Documentation Directory
- docs/
  ├── api/: API documentation
  ├── guides/: User guides and tutorials
  ├── reference/: Technical reference
  ├── development/: Development documentation
  ├── examples/: Code examples and sample projects
  └── changelog.md: Version history and changes

### 8.3 API Documentation
- Organize by service/resource
- Include request/response examples
- Document error codes and responses
- Include authentication requirements

### 8.4 User Guides
- Organize by feature area
- Include step-by-step instructions
- Provide real-world examples
- Include troubleshooting sections

### 8.5 Technical Reference
- Detailed technical specifications
- Configuration options
- Environment requirements
- Integration points

### 8.6 Development Documentation
- Code structure and organization
- Build and deployment instructions
- Testing guidelines
- Development environment setup

### 8.7 Examples
- Organize by use case
- Include complete working examples
- Document prerequisites
- Include setup instructions

### 8.8 Additional Files
- CONTRIBUTING.md: Guidelines for contributing
- CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md: Project code of conduct
- LICENSE: Project license information
- SECURITY.md: Security guidelines and procedures
